-- GM borrows another $4 billion from Treasury
-- 
-- Fri May 22, 2009 6:05pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/05/22/us-gm-treasury-sb-idUSTRE54L6J120090522

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - General Motors Corp on Friday said it had borrowed another $4 billion from the U.S. Treasury, taking its total federal funding to $19.4 billion. 

 In a filing with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, GM also said it expected to need another $7.6 billion from the U.S. Treasury after June 1. GM did not detail its plans for the additional loans but said it had provided a statement on its intended use of the funds to U.S. Treasury officials who approved the funding.